xt\",\"text\":\"**Investigating Java test results**\\n\\nI’m thinking that maybe the Java test didn’t use an agent, which could mean the dynamic access report is stemming from a native compile/run. There could be a native failure in `Report.<clinit>`, but perhaps that went unobserved. I should really inspect the test results from the JVM after the second run to see what’s going on. It sounds like a good place to start!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_UU6x2fko1k7SP7LAREkLBMo1|fc_05d581b97d6180010169fb9445fdf88191a92009175d162e2c", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/jtidy/jtidy/4aug2000r7-dev/build/test-results/test/TEST-jtidy.jtidy.ReportTest.xml", "limit": 100}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1829, "output": 991, "cacheRead": 30720, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 33540, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778095156263, "responseId": "resp_05d581b97d6180010169fb9435768081919fc6d6d0848133ec"}}
