[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Explaining testing scenarios**\n\nI need to ensure my test passes even when metadata is absent, but I can't just skip or not support missing metadata. I wonder if I could catch an error from MissingResourceException. The rules seem to indicate that for ordinary resources, dynamic-class-loading patterns shouldn't be used. But if I could catch that exception, it might let the test pass, though it wouldn't really validate behavior. I think I should consider that resources need to function under native conditions. So, how should I approach this?\n\n**Investigating Java test results**\n\nI’m thinking that maybe the Java test didn’t use an agent, which could mean the dynamic access report is stemming from a native compile/run. There could be a native failure in `Report.<clinit>`, but perhaps that went unobserved. I should really inspect the test results from the JVM after the second run to see what’s going on. It sounds like a good place to start!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_05d581b97d6180010169fb943634088191ab21fd387f199e95\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-5RFuPhVAfzr8YmW94xTGnx7pBYVkxrP7nDesdub7C14w5mRAsfd5l2vxIO5QrtcPSIouGwaiKyVhehbpjKMscI_3DJAlWeLE_RTkqJPswaFKy4ITRm5iBMBZQGrhNOmX4hfYQYFarx2ifaaMRwfKiEv_hrvzkPgJLApvFdzXrE7xBp7KDlN3HwUwd5q9c-CTRHRyjASQ7CZ82H119INsT7KprSGS9YSdooDyH0AyFj9j6pHxhdqPyAAuYwz-YqlZOp8m-Z29zSWAFeTupag-WQBaaeFS0wRqUEqgMQTBv2tOBHTmT6UxwkbcOnhgZGBRjwLFF-nssPLXlkMvpPpJMLx0dE-pUT6i_C2qtHPMWMQ6u9M2azH9CIBseEON0FrBndVsl-VTk6iJkP3xbbZeSzn9FQ__34zyyGUcczOk22-6v6AWRu2VGe3h3-n24_7ONFhXXEY330I5ILFqALsQa_ys6CAOLV7IOS-cSR6bNecM1OS3OocyWfUNTY13S3SP1DAcYe3kZcA2VUBC-MUTyrodTl_Mm_j0kvXpQkdo7wLQRDsQmkhJE5BFmxsHb6D67wdqXX0f425ZAcxGsxC3chtRXVb-dz32-UnI7gevoj3LJ2AHLG4dNvuSpzJk6LAxf9fisgLgaeqweJKtrhwnCzj8pmcCfv7ifoHPR8QjmSpcg2_hoCcFChIrYGafXyPKViUxkjbDt86br_m453vz-Pi-qYFoC3U9M9C12wl_1tjfsLZso4sAdkf9Pe3l97rcbqDYaM1d0UhG76OxBfCCB